		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Criticism of religion</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:277px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Imagine_no_religion.jpg" class="image" title="A sign that criticizes religion and draws attention to the September 11 attacks, by the Connecticut Valley Atheists in Rockville's Central Park, Vernon in December 2007.  The group issued an explanatory press release that stated &quot;[c]learly, 9/11 is the work of fanatics. However, we feel that religion even in moderation provides a foundation for fanatical groups to thrive.&quot;[1]"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/30/Imagine_no_religion.jpg" width="275" height="365" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Imagine_no_religion.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
A sign that criticizes religion and draws attention to the <a href="/wiki/September_11_attacks" title="September 11 attacks">September 11 attacks</a>, by the Connecticut Valley Atheists in Rockville's Central Park, <a href="/wiki/Vernon,_Connecticut" title="Vernon, Connecticut">Vernon</a> in December 2007. The group issued an explanatory press release that stated "[c]learly, 9/11 is the work of fanatics. However, we feel that religion even in moderation provides a foundation for fanatical groups to thrive."<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></div>
