<p><b>Criticism of religion</b> involves <a href="/wiki/Criticism" title="Criticism" class="mw-redirect">criticism</a> of the concept of <a href="/wiki/Religion" title="Religion">religion</a>, the validity of religion, the practice of religion, and the consequences of religion.</p>
<p>Religious criticism has a long history, going back as far as the first century B.C.E. in Rome and continuing to the present day with the advent of <a href="/wiki/New_atheism" title="New atheism">New atheism</a>. Religion has been alleged by critics to be harmful to the individual and to society, and to promote irrationality.</p>
