<li id="cite_note-117"><b><a href="#cite_ref-117" title="">^</a></b> Nobel Peace Laureate, Muslim and human rights activist <a href="/wiki/Shirin_Ebadi" title="Shirin Ebadi">Dr Shirin Ebadi</a> has spoken out against undemocratic Islamic countries justifying "oppressive acts" in the name of Islam. Speaking at the Earth Dialogues 2006 conference in Brisbane, Dr Ebadi said her native Iran as well as Saudi Arabia, Kuwait and Yemen "among others" were guilty of human rights violations. "In these countries, Islamic rulers want to solve 21st century issues with laws belonging to 14 centuries ago," she said. "Their views of human rights are exactly the same as it was 1400 years ago."</li>
